    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis means the autocommands will be cleared and options will not be set if `au!`  is run before VimEnter (such as in the user's init.vim).\r\n\r\nRef: #26579\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun the following command in a terminal emulator that supports truecolor.\r\n`nvim --clean +'au!'`\r\n\r\n`:echo &termguicolors`\r\n\r\nWill show 0.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:echo &termguicolors` showing 1 (enabled) due to the default when truecolor support is detected.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2042+g28c183b38c Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1702233742\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux archlinux 6.6.7-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nArch User Repository",
